    <title type="html"><![CDATA[The Bowling Kata]]></title>
    <link href="http://sbowenwilliams.github.io/blog/2016/05/03/the-bowling-kata/"/>
    <updated>2016-05-03T20:35:41-05:00</updated>
    <id>http://sbowenwilliams.github.io/blog/2016/05/03/the-bowling-kata</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1>Getting in to the Mind of a Master</h1>

<p>A &lsquo;kata&rsquo; is defined as a &ldquo;system of individual training exercises for practitioners of karate and other martial arts&rdquo;. Programming isn&rsquo;t exactly martial arts, but as coders we can make use of our own form of kata.</p>

<p>A programming kata is a tool used to teach how to think the way a master thinks, to code as they code. It should be repeated, it should be memorized, and then it should be repeated again.</p>

<p>The Bowling Game Kata is a common one: testing and designing a bowling game from scratch. Let&rsquo;s get started:</p>

<h3>First Test</h3>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">describe</span> <span class="no">Game</span> <span class="k">do</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">it</span> <span class="s1">&#39;initializes a new game&#39;</span> <span class="k">do</span>
</span><span class='line'>    <span class="n">expect</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">subject</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to</span> <span class="n">be_an_instance_of</span> <span class="no">Game</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="k">end</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>When run it results in:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">bowling</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rb</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="ss">:in</span> <span class="sb">`&lt;top (required)&gt;&#39;: uninitialized constant Game (NameError)</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>So we should probably define a <code>Game</code> class huh?</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="k">class</span> <span class="nc">Game</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>That&rsquo;s enough to pass this first test!</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="no">Finished</span> <span class="k">in</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mo">0012</span><span class="mi">8</span> <span class="n">seconds</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">files</span> <span class="n">took</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">15122</span> <span class="n">seconds</span> <span class="n">to</span> <span class="nb">load</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="n">example</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span> <span class="n">failures</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<h3>Second Test</h3>

<p>We have a game that initliazes successfully. Now we need to be able to roll.</p>

<p><img src="http://seanbw.com/images/bowling.gif"></p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="n">it</span> <span class="s1">&#39;rolls a gutterball&#39;</span> <span class="k">do</span>
</span><span class='line'>  <span class="n">subject</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">roll</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Ruh roh!</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="no">Finished</span> <span class="k">in</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mo">0022</span><span class="mi">9</span> <span class="n">seconds</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">files</span> <span class="n">took</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">18318</span> <span class="n">seconds</span> <span class="n">to</span> <span class="nb">load</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="n">examples</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span> <span class="n">failure</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>




<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="no">Game</span> <span class="n">rolls</span>
</span><span class='line'>     <span class="no">Failure</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="ss">Error</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">subject</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">roll</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>     <span class="ss">NoMethodError</span><span class="p">:</span>
</span><span class='line'>       <span class="n">undefined</span> <span class="nb">method</span> <span class="sb">`roll&#39; for #&lt;Game:0x007fbb339d71f0&gt;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="sb">     # ./bowling.rb:11:in `</span><span class="n">block</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="n">levels</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">in</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">top</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">required</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="err">&#39;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Let&rsquo;s write ourselves a roll method for Game. Roll should take the number of pins knocked down in that roll.</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">roll</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">number_pins</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'><span class="k">end</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>And with that we&rsquo;re now green again!</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='ruby'><span class='line'><span class="no">Finished</span> <span class="k">in</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mo">001</span> <span class="n">seconds</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">files</span> <span class="n">took</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="mi">14113</span> <span class="n">seconds</span> <span class="n">to</span> <span class="nb">load</span><span class="p">)</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="n">examples</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span> <span class="n">failures</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>This is a good foundation from which to continue the kata!
To be continued&hellip;</p>
]]></content>
